Observations per dose level

Source: R/nif_exploration.R
obs_per_dose_level.Rd

The total number of observations, per dose level and analyte.

Usage

obs_per_dose_level(obj, analyte = NULL, group = NULL)

Arguments

obj

A NIF object.

analyte

The analyte as character. If NULL (default), all analytes are selected.

group

An (optional) grouping variable as character. Defaults to 'NULL'.

Value

A data frame.

Examples

obs_per_dose_level(examplinib_poc_nif)
#>    DL    ANALYTE   N
#> 1 500     RS2023 672
#> 2 500 RS2023487A 672
obs_per_dose_level(examplinib_sad_nif)
#>     DL ANALYTE   N
#> 1    5  RS2023  51
#> 2   10  RS2023  51
#> 3   20  RS2023  51
#> 4   50  RS2023  51
#> 5  100  RS2023 102
#> 6  200  RS2023  51
#> 7  500  RS2023 306
#> 8  800  RS2023 102
#> 9 1000  RS2023  51
obs_per_dose_level(examplinib_poc_nif, group = "SEX", analyte = "RS2023")
#>    DL ANALYTE SEX   N
#> 1 500  RS2023   1 294
#> 2 500  RS2023   0 378
